msgctxt "sn35.130:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.130:0.2"
msgid "13. Gahapativagga "
msgstr "13. Householders "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 130. Hāliddikānisutta → haliddako (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.130:0.3"
msgid "130. Hāliddikānisutta "
msgstr "130. With Hāliddikāni "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.115, sc1
#. VAR: kuraraghare → kulaghare (s1-3, mr)
#. VAR: papāte → pavatte (bj, pts1) | sampavatte (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "sn35.130:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā mahākaccāno avantīsu viharati kuraraghare papāte pabbate. "
msgstr "At one time Venerable Mahākaccāna was staying in the land of the Avantis near Kuraraghara on Steep Mountain. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: hāliddikāni → hāliddakāni (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn35.130:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho hāliddikāni gahapati yenāyasmā mahākaccāno tenupasaṅkami … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho hāliddikāni gahapati āyasmantaṃ mahākaccānaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then the householder Hāliddikāni went up to Venerable Mahākaccāna … and asked him, "

msgctxt "sn35.130:1.3"
msgid "“vuttamidaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā: "
msgstr "“Sir, this was said by the Buddha: "

msgctxt "sn35.130:1.4"
msgid "‘dhātunānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattaṃ; phassanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati vedanānānattan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Diversity of elements gives rise to diversity of contacts, and diversity of contacts gives rise to diversity of feelings.’ "

msgctxt "sn35.130:1.5"
msgid "Kathaṃ nu kho, bhante, dhātunānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattaṃ; phassanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati vedanānānattan”ti? "
msgstr "How does diversity of elements give rise to diversity of contacts, and diversity of contacts gives rise to diversity of feelings?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: sukhavedaniyañca → sukhavedanīyañca (bj) | sukhavedanīyaṃ (si) | sukhavedaniyaṃ (s1-3, km, mr) | sukhavedaniyaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.130:1.6"
msgid "“Idha, gahapati, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā ‘manāpaṃ itthetan’ti pajānāti cakkhuviññāṇaṃ sukhavedaniyañca. "
msgstr "“Householder, it’s when a mendicant sees a sight and understands it to be agreeable. "

# NOTE: The syntax of this sentence is unclear, see BB’s note.
msgctxt "sn35.130:1.7"
msgid "Phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhā vedanā. "
msgstr "There is eye consciousness; and pleasant feeling arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as pleasant. "

#. VAR: paneva → panevaṃ (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "sn35.130:1.8"
msgid "Cakkhunā kho paneva rūpaṃ disvā ‘amanāpaṃ itthetan’ti pajānāti cakkhuviññāṇaṃ dukkhavedaniyañca. "
msgstr "Then they see a sight and understand it to be disagreeable. "

msgctxt "sn35.130:1.9"
msgid "Phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dukkhā vedanā. "
msgstr "There is eye consciousness; and painful feeling arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as painful. "

#. VAR: upekkhāṭṭhāniyaṃ → upekhāṭhānīyaṃ (bj) | upekkhaṭṭhāniyaṃ (s1-3) | upekhāṭṭhāniyaṃ (pts1) | upekkhāvedaniyaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "sn35.130:1.10"
msgid "Cakkhunā kho paneva rūpaṃ disvā ‘upekkhāṭṭhāniyaṃ itthetan’ti pajānāti cakkhuviññāṇaṃ adukkhamasukhavedaniyañca. "
msgstr "Then they see a sight and understand it to be a basis for equanimity. "

msgctxt "sn35.130:1.11"
msgid "Phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati adukkhamasukhā vedanā. "
msgstr "There is eye consciousness; and neutral feeling arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as neutral. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.116, sc2
msgctxt "sn35.130:2.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, gahapati, bhikkhu sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe … "
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant hears a sound with the ear … "

msgctxt "sn35.130:2.2"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … pe … "
msgstr "smells an odor with the nose … "

msgctxt "sn35.130:2.3"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … pe … "
msgstr "tastes a flavor with the tongue … "

msgctxt "sn35.130:2.4"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … pe … "
msgstr "feels a touch with the body … "

msgctxt "sn35.130:2.5"
msgid "manasā dhammaṃ viññāya ‘manāpaṃ itthetan’ti pajānāti manoviññāṇaṃ sukhavedaniyañca. "
msgstr "knows a thought with the mind and understands it to be agreeable. "

msgctxt "sn35.130:2.6"
msgid "Phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhā vedanā. "
msgstr "There is mind consciousness; and pleasant feeling arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as pleasant. "

msgctxt "sn35.130:2.7"
msgid "Manasā kho paneva dhammaṃ viññāya ‘amanāpaṃ itthetan’ti pajānāti manoviññāṇaṃ dukkhavedaniyañca. "
msgstr "Then they know a thought and understand it to be disagreeable. "

msgctxt "sn35.130:2.8"
msgid "Phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dukkhā vedanā. "
msgstr "There is mind consciousness; and painful feeling arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as painful. "

msgctxt "sn35.130:2.9"
msgid "Manasā kho paneva dhammaṃ viññāya ‘upekkhāṭṭhāniyaṃ itthetan’ti pajānāti manoviññāṇaṃ adukkhamasukhavedaniyañca. "
msgstr "Then they know a thought and understand it to be a basis for equanimity. "

msgctxt "sn35.130:2.10"
msgid "Phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati adukkhamasukhā vedanā. "
msgstr "Neutral feeling arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as neutral. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.130:2.11"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, gahapati, dhātunānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattaṃ; phassanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati vedanānānattan”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how diversity of elements gives rise to diversity of contacts, and diversity of contacts gives rise to diversity of feelings.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.130:2.12"
msgid "Sattamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

